<title>USA: Granite Construction sets share buyback.</title>
<headline>Granite Construction sets share buyback.</headline>
<dateline>WATSONVILLE, Calif. 1996-09-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Granite Construction Inc said its board of directors has authorized the company to repurchase about 100,000 shares of its own common stock on the open market during the next six months.</p>
<p>As of Aug 10, it had 18,121,253 shares of common stock outstanding.</p>
<p>Purchases will be made using the company's own cash resources. Shares repurchased will be held in the corporate treasury and will be used to cover future obligations under its future or current Employee Stock Ownership Plan (ESOP) or for other corporate purposes.</p>
</text>
